Amajita have progressed to the semifinals of the U20 AFCON following their convincing 3-1 win over Sudan on Sunday afternoon.South Africa broke the deadlock in the 11th minute through Phakamani Mahlambi. The Sudanese equalised in the 25th minute when Khaled Osman scored a beautiful goal.Thabo Senong s side restored their lead in the 60th minute when Kodisang&#8217;s close range shot was saved but Margeman was at the right place at the right time as he scored a nice goal from from 12-yards out.Amajita grabbed their final goal six minutes later through Mbatha. A win for South Africa sees themselve qualify for the FIFA U-20 World Cup, which will be held later this year in South Korea.